    "body": "You are trying to compare resample and interpolation which are completely different. Resample creates the bins according to the rule. If something falls in a bin then the how gets applied. This is really just a group-by.\n\nInterpolation on the other hand generates the bins and looks at ALL of them them to decide how to put the values.\n\nIf you want a generated point where you don't have a bin then interpolation is reasonable. If you want to reduce a bunch of points that are possibly irregular then resample is used.\n\n```\nIn [77]: df\nOut[77]: \n                     0   1   2\n2015-07-13 09:00:00  0  11   1\n2015-07-13 09:00:01  1  12   3\n2015-07-13 09:00:02  2  13   5\n2015-07-13 09:00:03  3  14   7\n2015-07-13 09:00:04  4  15   9\n2015-07-13 09:00:05  5  16  11\n2015-07-13 09:00:06  6  17  13\n2015-07-13 09:00:07  7  18  15\n2015-07-13 09:00:08  8  19  17\n2015-07-13 09:00:09  9  20  19\n\nIn [78]: df.resample(Timedelta('1.8s'),how='mean')\nOut[78]: \n                            0      1      2\n2015-07-13 09:00:00.000 0.500 11.500  2.000\n2015-07-13 09:00:01.800 2.500 13.500  6.000\n2015-07-13 09:00:03.600 4.500 15.500 10.000\n2015-07-13 09:00:05.400 6.500 17.500 14.000\n2015-07-13 09:00:07.200 8.000 19.000 17.000\n2015-07-13 09:00:09.000 9.000 20.000 19.000\n```\n"
  },
