    "body": "jreback:\nI am trying to resample in the signal processing sense of the word: I have a sampled signal of length N covering interval T, and I want to resample it to length K with the same interval, meaning the sampling rate changes from N/T to K/T. This is resampling as I know it. Obviously there is a jargon issue here.\nFrom what I can see,  pandas.resample is the only way to do that. pandas.interpolate cannot change the length of the DF. The problem is that pandas.resample loses too much information on the way.\n\nFinally, you will note that I compared in my own code the code that you did:\n`df.resample(Timedelta('1.8s'),how='mean')`\n\nHere is the plot output, and it's obviously wrong\n![figure_2](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/13135979/8698302/7a3e3cda-2b05-11e5-9ae5-eda3e1087f4a.png)\n\nFor example in 09:00:07.200  the value of series '0' is 8, but that is clearly wrong for a linear interpolation, since the value of the original DF is 8 on 09:00:08.\nThe value of the resampled df on 09:00:07.200 should be 7.2.\n"
