    "body": "The \"slowdown\" at the end comes from from us / scipy not _extrapolating_ outside the original bounds\n\n``` python\nIn [40]: df.reindex((df.index + td / 2) | df.index).interpolate().tail()\nOut[40]:\n                           0     1   2\n2015-07-13 09:00:07.500  7.5  18.5  16\n2015-07-13 09:00:08.000  8.0  19.0  17\n2015-07-13 09:00:08.500  8.5  19.5  18\n2015-07-13 09:00:09.000  9.0  20.0  19\n2015-07-13 09:00:09.500  9.0  20.0  19\n```\n\nI believe there's an option for this. For the non-even division.\n\n``` python\nIn [59]: length = 16\n\nIn [60]:     time_delta = (df.index[-1] - df.index[0]) / (length-1)\n\nIn [61]:     new_index = pd.date_range(start=df.index[0], end=df.index[-1], freq=time_delta)\n\nIn [62]: df.reindex(new_index).interpolate().plot()\n```\n\n![gh](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1312546/8698399/7837b296-2ac3-11e5-9cbf-6be93f4b5ced.png)\n\nYou might want to double check that the last one is identical to your example. It might not be. There's been some discussion about changing the way the interpolate API works, can't track it down now.\n"
